rComments: He is a bit slow and you will probably fall asleep in class. But, he goes straight to the point and he clearly tells you what he is looking for in the final exam. He is not there to trick you or try to make you fail. He is very knowledgeable and passionate about the materials.

Prof Oliver was very approachable, friendly and good at responding to emails. His grading/expectations were fair- he ran through several practice exams during the semester, which helped. His class wasn't the most interesting (con law II isn't generally), but he tried hard. The bilingual class was a bonus!

Had 3 classes with him and it took the 3rd one for me to finally understand what he expects as a professor. Very demanding, harsh but fair grader. He doesn't believe in one and only good answer; he is for very well backed up, logical and sound arguments. Don't be afraid to think outside the box as long as you can back it up with the authorities.

Il est gentil et il veux aider ses étudiants mais il a de la difficulté à capter l'attention des étudiants et de transmettre la matière de façon intéressante. La présentation de la matière manquait de la structure donc j'étais souvent perdu dans son cours...
